How to Maintain a git subtree
---------------------------

We maintain ip4r using git subtree. There is no need to do anything special if
you don't want to add/update a git subtree. But if you want to add a repo as a
git subtree. The following steps describes how.

1) Add the repo URL as a git remote.
   git remote add -f ip4r_remote git@github.com:RhodiumToad/ip4r.git
2) Clone the repo to a directory as a subtree.
   git subtree add --prefix gpcontrib/ip4r ip4r_remote master --squash
3) To update the subtree later:
   git fetch ip4r_remote master
   git subtree pull --prefix gpcontrib/ip4r ip4r_remote master --squash
4) Update subtree to a specific commit.
   git subtree merge --prefix gpcontrib/ip4r --squash commit_id
